 Centane - Centane police are investigating murder of a 30-year-old woman over the weekend. "It is alleged that the victim was left alone at her home by her sister on Saturday at Ngqokweni Locality, Holela Village, Centane," said police spokesperson, Captain Jackson Manatha. "When the sister came back, at about 21h00, on Saturday, she found her 30-year-old sister in a pool blood with multiple stab wounds on her upper body. "The motive behind the murder is not known." He said that Centane police are appealing to anyone with information to contact them at 047 498 1096 or 073 288 0340. "The information will be treated confidentially.  The identity of the deceased is still being withheld until all her relatives are officially informed of her murder." Acting Eastern Cape SAPS Provincial Commissioner, Major General Andries Swart, condemned the murder of the young defenceless woman. He vowed that Centane Police detectives will work around the clock to trace and arrest the suspect/s. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 